				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">......but dare not ask this on the Mage's board! <img src="images/smiles/icon_biggrin.gif" alt="Very Happy" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
The thing is, I am botting a Mage...... to my 58 Beastlord and now I would like to know which pet would be best for me to use, Fire, Water, Air or Earth.  I have done quit a lot of research to what each pet does and I know also about the focus items, but here's what I am looking for:
<br />

<br />
- Most damage output,
<br />
- Does not need to have high HP (my BL will have aggro at all times)
<br />
- Would like the pet to stun as much as possible
<br />
- No need for root (there's a druid in the mix too).
<br />
- no need for damageshield on pet (pet wont get hit)
<br />

<br />
This pretty much rules out the Earth pet, but I can't seem to figure out wether it's the Water pet with backstab? or the air pet with high attack, or the firepet with its nasty nuke that has the highest damage and the highest stun chance.
<br />

<br />
Do all these pets Bash, i.e. stun? And is the Air-pet nuke the only one that has a stun component? Can the airpet bash? 
<br />

<br />
Not sure how many flamers a "bots a mage" post would attract on the Mage forums, and since I am looking for some mature answers I ask this question to my friendly Beastlord brethen on these amiable forums. <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />

<br />
Thanks!
<br />

<br />
Bulge, 58 BL.<br />_________________<br />Bulge Trollson and Bulgette Trollson-V'Retta
