			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Greetings,
<br />

<br />
   In general you will want to use the Air pet in this combination.  The Water pet would give you higher DPS due to backstabs, however, the Air pet stuns would allow you to extend your Beastlord's battle readiness.
<br />

<br />
   With this duo, you would be relying on the Beastlord's heals, as such, stuns would be more efficient than the backstabs.
<br />

<br />
   When you get to the point where the Mage has suspend Minion 2, what you will want to do is summon and suspend a Fire pet, while still using the Air for most battles.   The reason for this is those situations where you need a super damage boost, simply lose the Air pet and unsuspend the Fire pet for the nuke fest, then resuspend the Fire and resummon an air when you go back to regular combat.
<br />

<br />
   The Air pet has a slightly higher DPS than a comparable leveled Beastlord warder.
<br />

<br />
   I should also point out that the Air pet tanks better than the Beastlord warder, however, for some reason the mobs will generally choose the Warder over the Air pet. The way to get around this, though I don't recomend it, is to turn /pet taunt off for the Warder.   The reason I don't recomend it is simply the heals that a Beastlord can use are more efficient.<br />_________________<br /><ul><li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67241">Elder Kaatt</a>, Sixty-Five Year Old Khati Sha Feral Lord of Xev.<li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=337255">Investigator Aaeorn</a>, Fifty-Fifth Circle Redeemed Thief Catcher of Xev.<li><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=362220">Aaeorm</a>, Enchantement Technician of the Fortieth Tier of Xev.</ul></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
