			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">My main is a mage (although my beasts may be changing that).  Anyhow, in most circumstances, I don't use the fire pet.  Most of the damage it does is from nuking, but tends to run out mana very fast.  Water is an average pet, but for the situation you described, I would use Air.  Air has decent damage and stuns.  I use Air in groups and Earth when I solo.  
<br />

<br />
Also, pet placement is important.  If you place Air behind or beside a mob, it will stun like crazy. This will interrupt spells and will save your tank from getting hit occasionaly, therefore requiring less healing.  True, it may not seem like much but over the course of a long battle it can really add up. 
<br />

<br />
Hope this helps! <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" /><br />_________________<br />Hanlaana Winterbourne and the 
<br />
Ever-faithful Fang
<br />
Beastlady of FV
<br />
Legacy of Sha</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
